Made a real spec-alignment pass, but not the full refactor end state.

The concrete change is that `happy-sync` no longer exports the legacy session-envelope API from its public surface, and the remaining legacy envelope helpers now live in CLI-local code instead. The shared package export surface is now centered on wire types, v3 protocol types, encryption, and `SyncNode` in [packages/happy-sync/src/index.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/index.ts#L1). I added the CLI-local legacy module in [packages/happy-cli/src/legacy/sessionProtocol.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/legacy/sessionProtocol.ts#L1), and rewired the legacy consumers to import from there, for example [packages/happy-cli/src/api/apiSession.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/api/apiSession.ts#L14) and [packages/happy-cli/src/agent/acp/AcpSessionManager.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/agent/acp/AcpSessionManager.ts#L1).

Verified:
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync build`
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:unit` -> 75 tests passed
- `yarn workspace happy-coder typecheck`
- `cd packages/happy-cli && npx vitest run src/claude/utils/v3Mapper.test.ts src/codex/utils/v3Mapper.test.ts src/agent/acp/AcpSessionManager.test.ts src/claude/utils/sessionProtocolMapper.test.ts src/codex/__tests__/sessionProtocolMapper.test.ts` -> 70 tests passed

This does not finish the entire plan. The repo still has broader legacy sync paths that the spec says should be removed, especially the app-side mixed `sync.ts` flow and remaining legacy CLI/session plumbing. The next highest-value slice is deleting or isolating those legacy runtime paths so `SyncNode` becomes the only active sync primitive end to end.
